race.comment: ELECTRIC ELVIS (1) is in an elite barn and just missed at Mornington first up. There was a stack of merit in the effort and he has more to give. Draws inside today and winning rider Childs sticks aboard. ULTRA BLUE (2) brought strong form to Terang on resumption and looked a run short off the longish break. He tumbles in grade with a handy 3kg claimer aboard and the longer sprint advantages. Is likely to control the race and will be hard to beat. NAVY NINA (7) resumes for a leading metro stable and has three jumpouts under her belt. Will race over further but has good ability and it won't surprise to see her wound up. MILITARY BASE (3) can use an inside barrier and is in the mix building on his Maiden win on debut. MORDIALLOC BEACH (11) deserves consideration at a price.
